  <text>
    <body>
      <div xml:id="song49">
        <head rend="italic">To a Lady weeping.</head>
         <head type="voice" rend="italic">For one, two or three Voyces.</head>
          <notatedMusic>
            <!-- MEI goes here -->
          </notatedMusic>
        <div type="underlay">
            <lg type="stanza">
              <l>O now the certain cause I know,</l>
              <l>whence the Rose and Lilly grow</l>
              <l>in your fair cheeks, the often showr's,</l>
              <l>which you thus weep do breed those Flow'rs.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <div>
           <lg type="stanza">
             <l>If that the flouds could <hi rend="italic">Venus</hi> bring,</l>
             <l>Or warlike <hi rend="italic">Mars</hi> from Flowers spring;</l>
             <l>Why may not hence two Gods arise?</l>
             <l>This from your Cheeks, that from your Eyes.</l>
           </lg>
        </div>
      </div>
    </body>
